>>What are Sequence-to-Sequence models?<<

(x) Models that map variable-sized inputs to variable-sized outputs {{Sequence-to-Sequence models feature a many-to-many structure, which allows for variable-sized inputs and outputs.}}
( ) Autoregressive RNNs {{Autoregressive RNNs are used as decoders, but there are other choices too. They are not Sequence-to-Sequence models by themselves.}}
( ) A three-component architecture: the encoder, decoder and RNN {{The Sequence-to-Sequence model usually has a two-component, encoder-decoder structure. Although RNNs feature heavily in Sequence-to-Sequence models, they are not a necessary component as the Transformer architecture has demonstrated. }}
( ) Models that map fixed-sized inputs to fixed-size outputs {{Sequence-to-Sequence models are made specifically to deal with variable-sized inputs and outputs.}}


